带健身环回家的17天：一个90后的家庭观察记录。
Bring home a fitness ring for 17 days: a home observation record after 90 days.
不懂。
I don't understand.
推游。
Push it.
*本文授权转载自公众号“我不懂你”。
* This article authorizes transliteration from the public label "I don't understand you."
我希望我所爱的人过得更好，也希望我用的是更好的方式。
I hope that the people I love are better off and that I am using a better way.
。
.
对于很多人来说，这都是一个过于漫长的“假期”。
For many, it was an excessively long "holiday."
。
.
除了对疫情的关注和担忧，“在家躺着就是做贡献”的我们，可能也没有想到，这会成为我们和父母在一起过得最长的一个春节。
In addition to the epidemic's concerns and concerns, "lying at home is contributing," we may not have expected that it would be the longest Spring Festival with our parents.
。
.
不过，对于把健身环带回家，并且满怀期待的我来说，这意料之外的17天，给了我许多惊喜和收获。
But for me, bringing home the gym rings and looking forward to it, the unexpected 17 days have been a lot of surprises and rewards for me.
。
.
这款带着健身功能的“游戏”，让我们全家都乐在其中，也让我的世界，对他们敞开了一角。
This "game" with a fitness function, let our family enjoy it, but also let my world, open a corner to them.
。
.
先夸十分钟健身环。
Brag about ten minutes of workouts.
“健身环大冒险”可能是2019年最出圈的“游戏”了（2020年很可能继续），之所以这么说，是因为它凭着自己“健身”的特性，从“主机游戏圈”一路火到了微博、小红书、微信……。
The Fitness Ring Adventure is probably 2019's hottest "game" (likely to continue in 2020), because of its "fitness" nature, from mainframe gaming to microblogging, red-letter writing, and tweeting...
毕竟，当它火了之后，很多人甚至不知道除了买它，还得另外买一台任天堂的游戏主机。
After all, when it got hot, many people didn't even know they would have to buy another Nintendo game console besides buying it.
。
.
为什么它会这么火？。
Why is it so hot?
当我玩了将近一个月，并用它成功地征服了家人之后，我觉得我……。
After playing for nearly a month and successfully conquering my family with it, I felt like...
找不到它不火的原因。
Can not find the reason why it is not hot.
。
.
在我看来，它有以下特点：。
In my opinion, it has the following characteristics:
1、操作简单——体感。
1. Operate simply - body feeling.
简单地说，就是你做什么，游戏里的人物就跟着做什么。
Simply put, what you do, the characters in the game do what you want.
。
.
几乎不需要学习任何额外的操作，什么手柄、按键、组合……不存在的。
There is almost no need to learn any extra operation, what handles, keys, combinations... no longer exist.
。
.
2、即时反馈——不让你的任何一个动作“白费”。
2. Instant feedback - don't let any of your actions go to waste.
在游戏里，手指一点，或者猛搓几分钟屏幕，游戏设计师就会用各种方式激情洋溢地告诉你：。
In the game, finger a little, or rub the screen for a few minutes, the game designer will tell you passionately in various ways:
你赢了！你成长了！你更强大了！。
You win! You're growing up! You're stronger!
相比起来，我们的学习和工作就“艰难”多了。
In contrast, our study and work are much more difficult.
。
.
而任天堂可贵的地方在于，它运用即时反馈，将游戏、冒险和运动结合了起来。
What Nintendo values is that it combines play, adventure and sport with instant feedback.
。
.
于是，你的每一个健身动作（哪怕是原地慢跑这么简单的动作），都会在游戏中得到体现和反馈。
Thus, every exercise you do (even a simple jog in place) is reflected and fed back into the game.
。
.
比如说，路上的金币和素材；时不时遇到的所谓“怪物”；你的经验值、等级和新的服装、新的技能。
For example, gold coins and fodder on the road; so-called "monsters" from time to time; your experience, grades and new clothes, new skills.
。
.
只要你在动作，你就会感觉自己“没有白做”，而是每一步都在成长。
As long as you are moving, you will feel that you are not doing it for nothing, but that you are growing with each step.
。
.
有这些设置，你再也不会每做一个深蹲或者抬腿时都在心里叫苦：好累啊，我还要做几个？。
With these settings, you'll never have to squat or raise your legs with a wail: How tired am I to do?
而是气汹汹地：“看我不把你打死！”。
Instead, he said angrily, "I will not kill you!"
3、贯穿游戏内外的激励系统——赞美！记录和反馈。
3. A motivational system throughout the game and beyond - praise! Recording and feedback.
赞美用了感叹号，是因为我发现，没有人不喜欢被赞美。
Compliments use exclamation points because I find that no one does not like to be praised.
。
.
这个游戏将“健身环”这个装置拟人化，叫“灵环”，它既是一个引导者，又是一个忠实的伙伴。
The game personifies the "fitness ring" device, called the "ring of spirits," which is both a guide and a loyal partner.
。
.
它从来不批评你、否定你，只是一直温柔、热情而坚定地引导和陪伴你。
It never criticizes you or denies you. It just guides and accompanies you gently, warmly and firmly.
。
.
动作不会？它绝不会厌烦，更不会嫌弃你；。
Action will not? It will never be bored, nor will it hate you;
做到一半难以坚持？它会耐心地等候你，并为你鼓劲；。
Is it half impossible to persevere? It waits patiently for you and cheers you up.
动作做得又标准又漂亮？。
Is the action standard and beautiful?
那完了，你会听到他的一百种花式赞美。
It's over, and you'll hear a hundred of his fancy compliments.
。
.
它的赞美并不空泛（你会觉得你值得），但也不包含任何附加条件。
Its praise is not empty (you might think you deserve it), but it contains no strings attached.
。
.
只要你这个动作做得好，它就会热情地称赞你：太棒了！Beautiful！。
If you do this right, it will enthusiastically praise you: This is great!
在游戏和动作引导方面，健身环也已经做到了一个“游戏软件”能做到的极致。
In the game and movement guidance aspect, the fitness ring has also achieved a "game software" can do the acme.
。
.
生动的画面、具体的示例、下方的提示、没做对时弹出的提示和中止——基本上，无论男女老少都可以逐渐掌握它的玩法。
Vivid pictures, concrete examples, tips below, pop-ups and pauses when not doing the right thing - basically, men and women of all ages can gradually master it.
。
.
最后还有记录。
And finally there is the record.
记录是一个常被人忽视和遗忘的好习惯。
Record keeping is a habit that is often ignored and forgotten.
在这里，每次结束，你所做动作的累积和新增次数都会被展现出来，达到一定的次数，还会给你相应的趣味称号。
At the end of each session, the number of actions you take and the number of times you add them will be displayed to a certain number of times and will give you interesting titles.
。
.
4、科学健康的运动理念——休息是为了更好地坚持。
4. Scientific and Healthy Exercise Idea - Rest is for better adherence.
在健身专业领域，已经有专业人士给出了好评：动作示范和设置都比较科学，里面的小知识也很正确；。
In the field of fitness professionals have given praise: action demonstrations and settings are more scientific, the little knowledge inside is also very correct;
而让我注意到的，是这款游戏的另一个理念：不必每天坚持，不必勉强，不管你中断了多久，再次回来，它依然会沿着上次的天数进行计算。
What I noticed was another idea for the game: don't hold on to it every day, don't force it, no matter how long you interrupt, and come back again, it will still count the same number of days before.
。
.
是哪种效果更好呢？。
Which effect is better?
是强调你必须每天坚持，中断一天就“重新再来”；还是如果你能够坚持，那当然非常好；但是你其实可以选择坚持或者中断。
It's an emphasis on whether you need to stick with it every day and start all over again after a break, or if you can stick with it, it's fine, but you can stick with it or stop it.
。
.
前一种隐含着对我们的不信任：如果我不强制你坚持，你肯定会放弃；。
The former implies a distrust of us: if I don't force you to insist, you are bound to give up.
但后一种，则给予了我们充分的信任和自由，同时也隐含着自信：我相信你会喜欢，会愿意坚持锻炼，因为这是你的选择，因为我足够吸引你。
But the latter gives us full trust and freedom and implies confidence: I believe you will like it and will stick to it, because it is your choice because I am attractive enough for you.
。
.
如果说任天堂推出“健身环大冒险”是为了满足玩家群体的“健身”需求，那么毫无疑问的是，它完全成功了。
If Nintendo launched the "fitness loop adventure" to meet the "fitness" needs of the player community, there is no doubt that it has been entirely successful.
。
.
事实上，只要你想过“锻炼”“健身”“减肥”，又因为种种原因难以坚持，那么你几乎不可能逃过健身环大冒险的魔爪。
In fact, if you've ever thought about exercising, working out, or losing weight, and it's hard to stick to it for a variety of reasons, it's almost impossible to escape the risk of a fitness loop.
。
.
反而，这款游戏对于先前已经在运动中找到了乐趣，或者早已是健身房常客的那些“肌肉爱好者”来说，倒不一定有很大的魅力。
Instead, the game isn't necessarily glamorous for "muscle buffs" who have previously had fun in sports, or who are already regular gym guests.
。
.
换而言之，它面向的就是普通人、业余爱好者，是有兴趣、有需要，却没有时间或条件的我们。
In other words, it is open to ordinary people, amateurs, is interested, need, but no time or conditions for us.
。
.
不过除了让我感受到运动的快乐，健身环还带给了我一些其他的感悟。
But in addition to making me feel the joys of exercise, the fitness ring brings me some other insights.
。
.
比如说，教育；。
Education, for example.
比如说，怎么和父母相处。
For example, how to get along with your parents.
。
.
在这里，我想说一说我把健身环带回家之后发生的故事。
Here, I'd like to tell you the story of what happened when I brought the gym ring home.
。
.
“不讲道理”，是我最后的坚持。
"unreasonable" is my last insistence.
玩到健身环的时候，我就意识到，它不仅适合我，更适合我的家人。
By the time I got to the gym, I realized that it was not just for me, but for my family.
。
.
如果说我还能办个健身房的卡，去请个私教，或者自己在网上搜到一套科学的运动课程对着练习；。
If I can get a gym card, get a personal tutor, or find myself doing a scientific exercise program online.
那么，在家乡那个十八线小城市，我的父母恐怕很难选择这些方式。
Well, in that 18-lane town back home, my parents probably had a hard time choosing these options.
。
.
他们比我更不愿意在这些方面花费太多，也不像我一样，能够方便快速地搜索到相关的资源。
They are more reluctant than I am to spend too much on these things, and do not have the same ease and speed with which I am able to find the relevant resources.
。
.
更关键的是，我之所以这么不爱运动也不擅长运动，当然不是没有原因的（笑）。
More importantly, the reason I'm so inactive is not good at sports, of course, not for no reason (laughter).
。
.
但是，我又非常清楚地意识到，他们确实需要一定时间的，相对规律和科学的锻炼。
However, I am also very clear that they do need a certain amount of time, relative discipline and scientific exercise.
。
.
因为职业原因，他们几乎都是长期伏案的脑力劳动者；有时候一坐下，埋头工作，一个半天或者一个晚上就过去了。
For professional reasons, they are almost all mental workers who sit down for long periods of time; sometimes a half-day or an evening passes as they sit down to work.
。
.
身体上，虽然没有什么大毛病，但一些慢性毛病一直在困扰他们：头疼、肠胃不好、失眠；。
Physically, there's nothing wrong with it, but there are chronic conditions that haunt them: headaches, a bad stomach, sleeplessness.
心理上，他们多少有些焦虑和情绪波动。
Psychologically, they are somewhat anxious and emotionally wobbly.
。
.
所有这些问题，都不是药物或者手术能够解决的。
None of these problems can be solved by drugs or surgery.
。
.
所有人（包括他们自己）也都会说：。
Everyone, including themselves, will also say:
要运动呀！要锻炼呀！。
Get some exercise! Exercise!
对啊，适度的锻炼当然对人的身体和心理都很有好处。
Yes, moderate exercise is good for your body and mind, of course.
。
.
但是，从说到做，有这么简单吗？。
But is it that easy to talk about doing?
“听过那么多的道理，却依然过不好这一生。
"I've heard so much, but I still don't have a good life.
”。
"
的确如此。
Indeed it is.
。
.
一直以来，我都不愿意再将“讲道理”这种交流方式沿用下去；。
For a long time, I would not like to "reason" this kind of communication way to continue;
所以，当我确实发现我的家人也需要运动时，我知道，和他们“苦口婆心”地讲：。
So, when I did find out that my family needed exercise, I knew, and they "bitterly complained."
“运动好运动棒”；。
Exercise is good exercise stick.
或者晓之以理动之以情地告诉他们：。
Or to tell them repeatedly.
“再不运动，身体就更差了”。
"If you don't exercise, your health will get worse.
“都是因为你不运动，所以才容易头疼”；。
It's all because you don't exercise that you get headaches.
又或者在他们不舒服的时候“冷眼嘲笑”：。
Or "cold-eyed ridicule" when they are uncomfortable.
“看吧？别人都没有感冒，就你感冒了，叫你不运动吧？”。
"See? Other people do not have a cold, you caught a cold, you do not exercise?"
之类，是不会有任何作用的。
Things like that won't work.
。
.
说得更严重一些，上面的这些交流方式，在我眼里，是居高临下、傲慢和“站着说话不腰疼”的。
To put it more seriously, the above modes of communication, in my opinion, are condescending, arrogant and "do not stand and talk waist pain."
。
.
更关键的，我和他们一样，也都需要锻炼、却同样没有成功坚持过；。
More importantly, like them, I also need to exercise, but have not succeeded in holding on to it.
所以，我更没有立场去这样“教育”他们。
Therefore, I have no position to "educate" them in this way.
。
.
于是，我一直在留意，也在思考，有什么办法，可能会让他们养成运动的习惯？。
So, I've been watching and thinking, what can be done to get them into the habit of exercise?
寻找这个答案的过程，我也有些焦虑；。
I am a little anxious about the process of finding this answer.
特别是看到他们抱怨自己不舒服时，我总会感到焦急和困扰：。
Especially when I see them complaining about their discomfort, I always feel anxious and upset.
该怎么办？。
What should I do?
直到健身环出现，我觉得，我找到答案了。
Until the gym rings show up, I think I've found the answer.
。
.
带回家，让他们也试试。
Take it home and let them try it.
。
.
不报任何期待，也许就能收获惊喜。
If you don't expect anything, you may be pleasantly surprised.
实话说，这次回家，健身环就是我最大的期待：。
To tell you the truth, this time home, the fitness ring is my biggest expectation:
我希望它能征服我的家人；。
I hope it will conquer my family.
虽然一个从来不玩游戏，甚至视游戏为仇敌；。
Although one never plays games, even considers the game as the enemy;
另一个虽然也玩点游戏，却十足是个傲娇直男。
The other, though he played a little game, was very proud and straight.
。
.
想安利这两个人，还真是有点难度。
It's kind of hard to think about Amway.
。
.
本来还想我亲自示范，结果没两分钟，我爸就把我赶下去了：。
I tried to do it myself, but in two minutes, my dad kicked me down.
我来试试！。
Let me try it.
我还挺开心，但是一上手，发现虽然它的操作在我眼里真的非常简单，但是在没有接触过这类产品的他们手中，还是有点困难。
I was happy, but once I started, I found that although it was really easy to operate in my eyes, but in the hands of those who did not have access to these products, it was a bit difficult.
。
.
我站在旁边，有点心急，但一直克制住自己想“伸手帮忙”的冲动。
I stood by, a little anxious, but restrained myself from the urge to "reach out".
。
.
因为很有意思的是：。
Because it's very interesting.
虽然每个人在教别人做什么事或者帮忙的时候，只要对方一时间没有学会，都本能地想要直接伸手；。
Although each person is teaching others to do something or to help, as long as the other side did not learn, instinctively want to reach out directly;
但一旦角色替换，自己成为那个在学习和摸索的人时，只要别人直接插手帮了自己，结局一定是失败的。
But once the character is replaced and he becomes the person who is learning and groping, as long as others intervene directly to help themselves, the end is certain to be a failure.
。
.
脾气好或者比较懒的人可能不介意别人“代劳”，但是他也肯定没有学到真正的知识；自尊心强或者脾气差一点的，还很可能当场生气。
A good-tempered or lazy person may not mind being "put to work," but he certainly does not learn real knowledge; a person with a high self-esteem or bad temper is more likely to be angry instantly.
。
.
显然，如果我强行“代劳”，那么他们很可能就会失去兴趣。
Obviously, if I impose "proxy work," they are likely to lose interest.
。
.
还好，磕磕绊绊地，我爸还是顺利地进入了冒险关卡。
Luckily, stumbling, my dad made it to the next level of adventure.
。
.
看着他有些笨拙地原地慢跑，然后学习着挤压和拉开环，获得路边的金币……我妈坐在沙发上，情不自禁地围观着我们。
Watching him jog a little clumsily in place, then learn to squeeze and pull the ring and get the gold coins by the side of the road... my mother sat on the sofa and couldn't help but watch us.
。
.
我趁机对她说，“你看，这个地图好看吧？”。
I took the opportunity to say to her, "Look, is this a good map?"
我妈矜持地点了点头。
My mother nodded her head in reserve.
。
.
等我爸打完一次怪兽，过完一个地图，可能是新鲜感过去，也可能是因为他还没习惯，玩得不太顺畅，于是，他选择让我妈来试试。
After my dad had played a monster and finished a map, maybe it was a new feeling or maybe he wasn't used to it, so he chose to let my mother try.
。
.
意料之中的，我妈以“这是给你们玩游戏的人设计的，我不会玩，我肯定玩不好”拒绝了。
Not surprisingly, my mother said, "This is for you who play games, I can't play, I must not play well" refused.
。
.
说实话，我的心在那一刻有点“凉”；。
To tell you the truth, my heart felt a little cold at that moment.
但我还是没有采取什么强制行为，只是安慰自己，不玩就不玩吧。
But I still did not take any enforcement action, just comfort themselves, do not play it.
。
.
不过，显然夫妻俩之间自有一套沟通方式，在我爸的不依不饶下，我妈傲娇地提出了几个要求，才终于答应下场一试。
However, it was clear that there was a way of communication between the couple, and with my father's obstinacy, my mother made a few arrogant requests and finally agreed to have a try.
。
.
健身环的魔力就在于，只要你开始尝试，你就几乎不可能放弃。
The magic of a fitness ring is that as long as you try, it's almost impossible for you to give up.
。
.
感受到自己的每一个动作都得到实时反馈，在“灵环”热情洋溢的赞美和鼓励下，我妈很快就适应了，而且有些动作比我爸还标准。
Feeling real-time feedback on every move she made, my mother quickly adapted to the warm praise and encouragement of the ring, and some of her moves were even more standard than my father's.
。
.
我的心情也像过山车一样起伏：。
My mood is like a roller coaster ride.
看来能行！。
It seems to work.
结果，两个人“试完”之后，都没有“欲罢不能”的意思。
As a result, neither of the two "tried it out" meant "can't give up."
。
.
我心里的过山车也一个猛子扎进地里了：。
The roller coaster in my heart also hurtled into the ground:.
看来还是不太行。
It still doesn't look good.
。
.
收拾好装备，我几乎已经放弃了。
Get your gear together. I've almost given up.
。
.
原本，在我的期待或者想象中，他们应该能很快上手，并且马上从中感受到乐趣，“欲罢不能”，还要给这个东西“点赞”。
Originally, in my expectation or imagination, they should be able to quickly, and immediately feel the fun, "can't stop," and give this thing "praise."
。
.
但是，现实似乎没有我想得这么“美好”。
But the reality doesn't seem as good as I thought.
。
.
他们还是有些不太明白操作规则，也没有表现出非常大的兴趣。
Still, some of them don't quite understand the rules of the game and don't show much interest.
。
.
——算了吧，不玩就不玩，勉强也没意思。
Come on, no fun, no fun, no fun at all.
。
.
转眼到了第二天，我还在床上睡觉时，忽然听到外面客厅里传来我熟悉的声音。
The next day, while I was sleeping in bed, I suddenly heard a familiar voice from the living room outside.
。
.
咦？。
Why?
本来，想在电视上运行健身环，还要把HDMI线拔出来插到底座的插口，还要按好几个键……之前这些都是我操作的，没想到他们已经玩上了？。
The idea was to run the ring on TV, pull the HDMI cord out of the socket and press several buttons... that was all I had done before, but they were already playing?
果然，客厅里，我爸已经再度拿起了健身环。
Sure enough, in the living room, my dad had picked up the gym ring again.
。
.
于是，这之后的每一天，我家都会响起健身环大冒险的声音。
Then, every day after this, my family will ring the sound of fitness ring adventure.
。
.
这一切和我想象的不一样，但却比我想象的更好、更真实：。
It was different from what I had imagined, but it was better and more real than I had imagined.
他们的确没有马上掌握操作方式，但是每一次都比上一次更熟练；。
They really don't know how to operate right away, but each time they're more adept than the last;
他们也没有和我一样，只专注于其中的冒险模式，而是兴致盎然地把什么都试了一遍，然后找到了各自最爱玩、最擅长的小游戏和模式；并且乐此不疲地开始彼此竞争、比赛，也非常友好地提示、帮助对方；。
They didn't focus on the adventure model, as I did, but they experimented with everything, then found their favorite little games and modes of play; and they happily began to compete with each other, to compete, to be friendly and to help each other;
看着他们完全地投入、沉浸在里面，为打倒了怪物而欢呼、为拿到了最高分而兴奋、为超过了对方而“耀武扬威”，为帮助对方而焦急地在场外连声提示、打气；。
Watching them fully immerse themselves in, cheering for the fall of the monster, excited to get the highest score, "swagger" to overtake each other, hurriedly yelling and cheering to help each other;
看到他们自己玩时，遇到困难的动作，又“气”又“恨”，却依然能咬牙坚持；在对方这样时，先是“幸灾乐祸”，但还是会由衷地鼓励、赞扬对方；。
When they see themselves playing, they encounter difficult movements, "qi" and "hate", but still be able to adhere to their teeth; when the other side of this, first, "gloating," but also heartily encourage, praise each other;
看到他们玩了半个小时、一个小时后浑身微汗、那种运动过后的快乐和成就感……。
See them play for half an hour, an hour later sweat, that kind of exercise after the joy and accomplishment...
我每次都会情不自禁地露出笑容。
Every time I smile, I can't help smiling.
。
.
实话说，这样的场景，在我家并不多见。
To tell you the truth, such scenes are rare in my family.
。
.
也是在他们游玩的过程中，我才发现，真的只有放下“期待”、放下自己的“想象”和“要求”，才能收获到真实和惊喜。
It is also in the course of their play, I found that really only put down "expectations", put down their "imagination" and "requirements," can be harvested real and surprised.
。
.
和眼前这样让人发自内心地喜悦和开心的画面比，我一开始的“想象”，多么单薄而脆弱。
How thin and fragile was my initial "imagination", compared to the present frame of mind-boggling joy and joy.
。
.
是“教育”，还是引导和支持。
Education, or guidance and support.
如我开头所说的那样，健身环本身，是一个非常有效的“培养健身兴趣和习惯”的产品。
As I said at the beginning, the fitness ring itself is a very effective "fitness interest and habits" product.
。
.
之所以能这么有效，是因为它遵循了一系列的理念，而这些理念，正是最好的“教育”方式。
What makes it so effective is that it follows a series of ideas that are the best way to "educate."
。
.
我们通常所说的“教育”，其实多少有些“居高临下”。
What we usually call "education" is actually somewhat condescending.
。
.
同样，我们所默认的教育方式，也一样充满了“说教”“灌输”的味道。
Similarly, the education method that we acquiesce to, also is full of "sermon" "indoctrinate" flavour.
。
.
它的本质在于，我们会把“教育”，当成是“上对下的传播”“有对无的灌输”。
Its essence lies in the fact that we will take "education" as "up-to-down transmission" and "indoctrination with nothing."
。
.
我们默认，“教育者”比“被教育者”懂得更多、更正确、更优势、也更优越。
By default, "educators" know more, are more right, have more advantage, and are better than the "educated."
。
.
被教育者则是无知的、不足的、茫然的、错误的、也是地位更低的。
The educated are ignorant, deficient, at sea, false, and of lower rank.
。
.
但是，这样是对的吗？。
But is that right?
或者说，这样的“教育”，能成功吗？。
Or, can such an "education" succeed?
健身环显然从未想过要“教育”它的玩家，它只是被设计出来，尽可能地让各种各样的人，都能最大化地感受到“运动”的乐趣和成就，从而主动地去坚持、去学习、去每天都要打开它，和它见面。
The gym obviously never wants to "educate" its players, it is just designed to maximize the fun and achievement of the sport for as many different people as possible, and to actively persevere, to learn, to open it up every day, to meet it.
。
.
我也一直在努力不去“教”我的父母玩健身环。
I have also been trying not to "teach" my parents to play the gym ring.
。
.
第二天开始，我就不再站在他们身边，紧张兮兮地等着“帮忙”。
The next day, I stopped standing next to them and waited nervously for help.
。
.
即使第一天的时候，他们都明显地表现出了不适应和不习惯。
Even on the first day, they were visibly uncomfortable and unaccustomed.
。
.
但是很快，我发现，开始的“不会”是真的，但他们探索和学习的速度也是真的。
But soon I found that the initial "no" was true, but the speed with which they explored and learned was also true.
。
.
特别是在没有我站在一边试图“帮忙”之后。
Especially after I stood by and tried to "help."
。
.
人本来就有好奇心。
Curiosity is inherent in man.
。
.
人也天然具有探索和学习的能力。
People also have the natural ability to explore and learn.
。
.
没有我的“指导”、没有我的“代劳”，他们会反复“犯错”，但是一旦成功，就几乎不会再忘记。
Without my "guidance" and my "agency," they would "err" repeatedly, but once they succeed, they would hardly ever forget.
。
.
学习新的动作时，我也想看到他们“一次性学会，动作完美又标准”；。
When learning new movements, I also want to see them "one-off learning, perfect and standard movements";
但是他们第一次是50分、60分、第二次、第三次就是80分、再之后就是90分、100分。
But the first time they scored 50 points, 60 minutes, the second time, the third time they scored 80 points, then 90 minutes and 100 points.
。
.
而我所做的，只是在他们需要的时候，在他们实在是搞不定的时候，在他们主动向我提问的时候，向他们示范或者讲解。
What I do is to demonstrate or explain to them when they need it, when they are really in doubt, when they ask me questions.
。
.
更多的时候，我的存在只是一种“支持”，即，他们需要帮忙的时候，有我在。
More often than not, my presence is just a form of "support," that is, they need help when I am with them.
。
.
这个过程当然需要时间；。
This process will of course take time.
但当他们完全不需要我，也能畅玩无阻的时候，我发现，我很快乐。
But when they don't need me at all and can play unimpeded, I find that I am happy.
。
.
我亲眼见证了他们面对新事物，自由地探索、尝试，在引导、支持和鼓励中，感受到喜悦和成长的过程。
I have witnessed them face to face with new things, freely explore, try, guide, support and encourage, feel the process of joy and growth.
。
.
这也是我玩健身环的过程。
This is how I play the gym ring.
。
.
所以，我最开始的“期待”，实现了。
So my initial "expectation" came true.
。
.
健身环的确征服了他们，也给我家带来了很多欢乐。
Fitness rings have really conquered them and brought a lot of joy to my family.
。
.
我很欣慰，也有些骄傲：这证明，我的坚持是对的。
I am delighted, and somewhat proud: it proves that I am right in my insistence.
。
.
似乎，我们这一代，长大后，和父母的相处和交流，总是有些别扭、僵硬甚至是冲突。
It seems that our generation, growing up with parents and communication, is always a bit awkward, rigid and even conflict.
。
.
我很早就发现，和他们说话，有时是“无话可说”，有时是“话不投机”。
I discovered early that talking to them was sometimes "speechless" and sometimes "unspeculative."
。
.
但是，我们之间，都依然真心地希望对方过得好，过得健康，过得快乐。
But, between us, still sincerely hope each other to live well, live healthily, live happily.
。
.
哪怕这一希望，往往就是引发冲突的根源。
Even that hope is often the source of conflict.
。
.
我理解，在父母那里，他们对我的希望，自有一番图景。
I understand that my parents had a vision of what they expected of me.
。
.
稳定的工作、稳定的伴侣、早日结婚、生子，成家立业。
A stable job, a stable partner, early marriage, children, starting a family.
。
.
过着这样的小日子，就是他们最大的期望。
To live such a small day is their greatest expectation.
。
.
其实在我这里，我也有对他们的希望。
In fact, here I am, I also have hope for them.
。
.
越是走入社会，就越能理解、也越心疼他们。
The more you go into society, the more you understand and love them.
。
.
所以，我反而希望，他们能多关心关心自己。
So, instead, I hope they care more about themselves.
。
.
我希望他们能找到自己的兴趣爱好、能有自己的生活、能把自己的健康放在心上。
I hope they can find their own interests, have their own lives, and take their own health to heart.
。
.
能像我一样，更自由、更快乐。
freer and happier than I am.
。
.
然而，有时候我会发现，其实，我们对父母的这份期待，就像父母对我们的期待一样，可能是一种“美好的强求”。
Sometimes, however, I find that this expectation of our parents, like what parents expect of us, can be a "beautiful compulsion."
。
.
想明白这一点后，我释然了很多。
I was relieved to know that.
。
.
那么，在他们真的有某些需求，而我又能找到更好的东西；。
Well, there's something they really need and I can find something better;
并且能用更好的方式分享给他们的时候；。
And be able to share them in a better way.
我们都会很开心吧？。
Are we all gonna be happy?
在这一点上，我正在努力尝试。
I am trying hard at this point.
。
.
有时候，我也会忍不住用过去的方式，用“居高临下”的、“不耐烦”的、“傲慢”的方式对待他们。
Sometimes I can't help but treat them in the same condescending, impatient, and arrogant way I used to.
。
.
但是带着健身环回家的这17天，它再次告诉我，哪种方式更好。
But after 17 days at home with a fitness ring, it's telling me again which way is better.
。
.
我们这一代人，可能都受过那一种“教育”，都被那样对待过（也可能现在还是）：。
My generation, perhaps, has all received one of those "educations" that have been (and may still be) treated in that way:
“被”认为冷、“被”认为饿、“被”认为“你需要被教育”；。
be considered cold, be thought hungry, be thought that you need to be educated.
而教育的方式，则是“讲大道理”“插手代劳”“放任不管”；。
And the way of education, is "to speak big principle" "to intervene in behalf of labor" "let go";
教育的态度，没有很多很多的鼓励、赞美，但有很多的指责、打击、甚至嘲笑和否定；。
The attitude of education, not a lot of encouragement, praise, but there are a lot of criticism, hit, even ridicule and negation;
如果我们还是小孩，我们只能乞求、愤怒、威胁父母，希望他们用这样的、更好的方式；。
If we are children, we can only beg, anger, and threaten our parents in this, better way;
但，我们已经独立、成年了。
But we are independent and grown up.
。
.
所以，如果有更好的方式，我想，那或许应是我们的责任了。
So if there is a better way, I think it might be our responsibility.
。
.
很遗憾的是，如今健身环因为种种原因，很难及时买到。
Unfortunately, fitness rings are hard to get in time for a variety of reasons.
。
.
等疫情过去，下次回家，我打算带一套新的给他们。
When the outbreak is over, next time I go home, I plan to bring them a new set.
。
.
虽然我从来没有问过他们对健身环的感受，但是我想，无论如何，他们的确体验到了运动带来的乐趣。
I never asked them how they felt about the ring, but I think they did experience the joy of exercise anyway.
。
.
我也从未期待健身环的出现能够带来什么惊天动地的改变（比如让他们变成健身狂魔），但是我想，下一次，我邀请他们运动时，他们一定不会再那么迟疑。
I never expected the ring to make a difference (like turning them into a fitness zealot), but I think the next time I invite them to exercise, they won't be so hesitant.
。
.
对于他们，这个上手简单、即玩即放、自由有趣的“游戏”，是我作为子女给他们的心意，也是我作为成人的一个坚持：。
For them, this simple, playful, free and fun "game" is what I give them as a child, and one that I insist on as an adult.
我希望我所爱的人过得更好，也希望我用的是更好的方式。
I hope that the people I love are better off and that I am using a better way.
。
.
健身环也许不是一个普遍适用的标准答案，但我们的态度和尝试，才是关键。
Fitness rings may not be a universal standard answer, but our attitudes and attempts are the key.
。
.
